Line 1: Imports the dart:convert library for UTF-8 and Base64 encoding/decoding.
Line 2: Imports the dart:math library to access secure random number generation.
Line 3: Imports the dart:typed_data library for working with byte lists (Uint8List).
Line 5: Imports the PointyCastle library, which provides cryptographic algorithms for Dart.
Line 7: Defines the AESService class responsible for symmetric encryption.
Line 10: Defines the generateKey method to create a 256-bit (32-byte) AES key.
Line 11: Creates a cryptographically secure random number generator.
Line 12-14: Generates a list of 32 random bytes and converts it to a Uint8List.
Line 17: Defines the generateIV method to create a 128-bit (16-byte) Initialization Vector.
Line 18: Creates a secure random number generator.
Line 19-21: Generates a list of 16 random bytes and converts it to a Uint8List.
Line 24: Defines the encrypt method which takes plaintext and a key, returning a map with the ciphertext and IV.
Line 26: Generates a new random IV for this specific encryption operation.
Line 28: Instantiates a PaddedBlockCipher using AES in CBC mode with PKCS7 padding.
Line 29-35: Initializes the cipher for encryption (true) using the provided key and the generated IV.
Line 37-39: Converts the plaintext string to bytes and processes it through the cipher.
Line 41-44: Returns a map containing the base64-encoded ciphertext and the base64-encoded IV.
Line 47: Defines the decrypt method which takes ciphertext, a key, and a base64-encoded IV.
Line 49: Decodes the base64 IV string back into a Uint8List.
Line 51: Instantiates the PaddedBlockCipher with the same AES/CBC/PKCS7 configuration.
Line 52-58: Initializes the cipher for decryption (false) using the key and the decoded IV.
Line 60: Decodes the base64 ciphertext and processes it through the cipher to retrieve the original bytes.
Line 62: Converts the decrypted bytes back into a UTF-8 string and returns it.
